description.excerpt: This is a GraphNeuralNetwork based project to predict the demanding of vehicle amount when by inputing timestamp, this repository focus on "How to Preprocssing, Traning and Evaluating on baselines". However, there is another frontend, Node-javascript based project, to show a Visualization demo, if you interest Visualization Project & Demo A large amount of yellow cab data from New York City is available to the public. Each trip record contains the latitude and longitude of the pickup and dropoff locations, the date and time of the pickup and dropoff, and additional information. We will construct a grid over NYC and create undirected graphs where an edge represents a trip between two points on the grid. The goal is to feed these graphs (each graph constituting one trip from starting to its end) into an GNN network in order to predict the next demand hotpot step1, cluster by gridbased region, see as the deepmind's
Additional, we also use an animation to show the individual route lane at demand area after predicting
